{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-1073"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Cocoa, Chocolate and Sugar Confectionery Manufacturing Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1073"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :food/cocoa-chocolate-confectionery-manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:food-security :food-safety :fair-labor]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :chocops-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization :telemetry]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "ChocOpsAdvisor ⊣ Chocolate Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, chocops.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (chocops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore and a DatomicStore
 backed by langchain.db via langchain-store.core). A back-office PLANT
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for cocoa/chocolate/sugar-confectionery
 manufacturing -- not direct conching/tempering/molding-line equipment
 control and not food-safety certification authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-food-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. 18+ HARD invariants (op-not-allowed,
 effect-not-propose, batch-not-registered, no-spec-basis,
 evidence-incomplete, moisture/cocoa-content/particle-size/process-temp/
 cadmium/viscosity out-of-window, foreign-material-detected,
 metal-detector-calibration-overdue, weight-variance-excessive,
 allergen-label-mismatch, sanitation-score-insufficient,
 food-safety-flag-unresolved, already-processed,
 already-shipment-finalized) elaborate this blueprint's Governor.
 `:log-production-batch` and `:coordinate-shipment` (the two real
 actuation events) plus `:flag-food-safety-concern` ALWAYS escalate to
 a human plant operator via the compiled graph's `:request-approval`
 node (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based resume); only
 `:schedule-maintenance` is eligible to auto-commit when the Governor
 is clean. Every commit/hold/approval-rejected decision lands in the
 append-only ledger, and an approved `:log-production-batch` /
 `:coordinate-shipment` also flips the batch's `:processed?` /
 `:shipment-finalized?` flag on the Store -- 58 tests / 207 assertions
 green (`clojure -M:dev:test`), demo runnable end-to-end against both
 Store backends (`clojure -M:dev:run`)."}
